You know, I never thought of that. I had a 65 crewcab but never really
explored underneath as much as I could have. Generally, if everything is
working right, there is no reason to find out why !

I wanted everyone to make sure that when I referred to "duct tape" I meant
the metal kind, not the cloth kind. I found that the adhesive backing sticks
for extended lengths of time in varying temperatures without coming loose,
since it was intended for heating system ducts anyway.
